                            <comment id="13036122" author="jukkaz" created="Thu, 19 May 2011 12:42:30 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;As a first step I&apos;d simply make the runnable tika-app jar available as a direct download from the download page.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To do this we can take the already released tika-app-0.9.jar from Maven central, put it in the dist folder, and apply the attached patch. I suppose no new release vote is needed since no bits are changed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Unless anyone sees problems with this I&apos;ll make the changes tomorrow.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13036793" author="jukkaz" created="Fri, 20 May 2011 13:17:51 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I added the tika-app jar to downloads and in revision 1125344 I modified the release build to automatically prepare a release candidate folder with the source archive and the tika-app jar in it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t think there&apos;s too much of a demand for direct downloads of the individual components or the javadocs, as the former are easily available from Maven Central (or as an aggregate in the tika-app jar for Ant users) and the latter are published on the Tika web site.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thus resolving as fixed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13036852" author="chrismattmann" created="Fri, 20 May 2011 15:39:23 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 you rock, thanks Jukka!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
